WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:30.378 align:middle line:90%


00:00:30.378 --> 00:00:32.868 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:32.868 --> 00:01:00.330 align:middle line:90%


00:01:00.330 --> 00:01:03.650 align:middle line:84%
>> When I stepped out of the cab
in Brooklyn, I didn't know it,

00:01:03.650 --> 00:01:06.490 align:middle line:84%
but I was about to
meet Glenda the Good.

00:01:06.490 --> 00:01:09.710 align:middle line:84%
You know, the witch who pranced
through enchanted poppy fields

00:01:09.710 --> 00:01:11.300 align:middle line:90%
in the north of Oz?

00:01:11.300 --> 00:01:13.005 align:middle line:90%
You get a pair of ruby slippers.

00:01:13.005 --> 00:01:15.286 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:15.286 --> 00:02:20.485 align:middle line:90%


00:02:20.485 --> 00:02:23.180 align:middle line:90%
Her real name was Val Gente.

00:02:23.180 --> 00:02:25.520 align:middle line:84%
And she was raised on
the island of Haiti,

00:02:25.520 --> 00:02:28.240 align:middle line:84%
not with a litter of
prune-faced munchkins.

00:02:28.240 --> 00:02:31.108 align:middle line:90%


00:02:31.108 --> 00:02:34.070 align:middle line:84%
Val used the ancient skills
of the ritual drummer

00:02:34.070 --> 00:02:37.760 align:middle line:84%
with the tools of the
DJ in the digital age.

00:02:37.760 --> 00:02:40.070 align:middle line:84%
She was a sorcerer
of shamanic talent

00:02:40.070 --> 00:02:43.430 align:middle line:84%
with a gift for speaking to
both the living and the dead.

00:02:43.430 --> 00:02:49.730 align:middle line:90%


00:02:49.730 --> 00:02:52.580 align:middle line:10%
I was impressed,
but I also realized

00:02:52.580 --> 00:02:55.970 align:middle line:10%
this was just the first
of my long journey.

00:02:55.970 --> 00:02:59.780 align:middle line:84%
It was an initiation,
my ruby moment.

00:02:59.780 --> 00:03:03.543 align:middle line:84%
>> You'll have to cue me,
because I can go on and on.

00:03:03.543 --> 00:03:16.110 align:middle line:90%


00:03:16.110 --> 00:03:18.210 align:middle line:84%
>> This space is
totally energized.

00:03:18.210 --> 00:03:21.570 align:middle line:90%


00:03:21.570 --> 00:03:26.690 align:middle line:84%
I have experienced that in
certain other circumstances.

00:03:26.690 --> 00:03:28.800 align:middle line:10%
But I've only noticed
energy like this, like,

00:03:28.800 --> 00:03:30.400 align:middle line:10%
walking into very old churches.

00:03:30.400 --> 00:03:33.480 align:middle line:90%


00:03:33.480 --> 00:03:34.290 align:middle line:90%
it's electric.

00:03:34.290 --> 00:03:36.900 align:middle line:90%
It's very electric.

00:03:36.900 --> 00:03:38.680 align:middle line:90%
Very calming.

00:03:38.680 --> 00:03:45.070 align:middle line:84%
Of course, there's a whole
thing about art, spirituality,

00:03:45.070 --> 00:03:46.385 align:middle line:90%
religion, magic.

00:03:46.385 --> 00:03:48.744 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:48.744 --> 00:04:12.330 align:middle line:90%


00:04:12.330 --> 00:04:16.019 align:middle line:84%
>> If you put your hands close
to a speaker while there's some

00:04:16.019 --> 00:04:18.839 align:middle line:84%
heavy bass, you're going to
feel something in your hands.

00:04:18.839 --> 00:04:20.160 align:middle line:90%
That's frequency.

00:04:20.160 --> 00:04:25.170 align:middle line:84%
That's the physical
manifestation of frequency.

00:04:25.170 --> 00:04:27.060 align:middle line:84%
So there's some energy
coming out of there

00:04:27.060 --> 00:04:31.350 align:middle line:84%
that you can't see, but you feel
it in your hands sort of thing.

00:04:31.350 --> 00:04:38.130 align:middle line:84%
So frequencies, coming from the
Haitian culture, the Haitian

00:04:38.130 --> 00:04:43.920 align:middle line:84%
Voodoo culture, we're dealing
with so specific rhythm

00:04:43.920 --> 00:04:45.810 align:middle line:90%
patterns, specific chants.

00:04:45.810 --> 00:04:51.300 align:middle line:90%


00:04:51.300 --> 00:04:52.920 align:middle line:84%
So it's already
kind of pre-coded.

00:04:52.920 --> 00:04:55.164 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:55.164 --> 00:05:05.370 align:middle line:90%


00:05:05.370 --> 00:05:10.920 align:middle line:84%
And certain songs you don't
sing after 3:00 PM on Thursdays,

00:05:10.920 --> 00:05:12.370 align:middle line:90%
you just don't.

00:05:12.370 --> 00:05:14.130 align:middle line:84%
And everyone knows
not to sing it,

00:05:14.130 --> 00:05:16.350 align:middle line:84%
because there's a
frequency in that song

00:05:16.350 --> 00:05:18.300 align:middle line:90%
that you don't want to manifest.

00:05:18.300 --> 00:05:25.330 align:middle line:84%
So pretty much, the sound
manifests in physical reality.

00:05:25.330 --> 00:05:27.090 align:middle line:84%
So the sound that
I'm creating in here

00:05:27.090 --> 00:05:28.305 align:middle line:90%
is also what you're feeling.

00:05:28.305 --> 00:05:31.170 align:middle line:90%


00:05:31.170 --> 00:05:35.420 align:middle line:84%
So when you walk into
the church or the temple,

00:05:35.420 --> 00:05:38.510 align:middle line:84%
because the frequency
is still there,

00:05:38.510 --> 00:05:41.810 align:middle line:84%
there's a remnant of
it that's in the space.

00:05:41.810 --> 00:05:45.320 align:middle line:90%
And it stays there.

00:05:45.320 --> 00:05:47.260 align:middle line:90%
You can't really get rid of it.

00:05:47.260 --> 00:05:50.615 align:middle line:84%
It becomes part of the
fabric of that space.

00:05:50.615 --> 00:05:56.750 align:middle line:90%


00:05:56.750 --> 00:05:59.720 align:middle line:84%
>> This is the
house I grew up in.

00:05:59.720 --> 00:06:02.390 align:middle line:84%
It sits on a patch of
overly taxed landfill

00:06:02.390 --> 00:06:06.030 align:middle line:90%
in Hamden, Connecticut.

00:06:06.030 --> 00:06:08.790 align:middle line:84%
I've sailed to South
and Central America.

00:06:08.790 --> 00:06:12.570 align:middle line:84%
I've lived in Los Angeles,
New York, and Montreal.

00:06:12.570 --> 00:06:15.480 align:middle line:90%
Finally, I settled in Berlin.

00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:18.970 align:middle line:10%
After 10 amazing years
in that city of ravens,

00:06:18.970 --> 00:06:21.940 align:middle line:10%
a place I felt was
my natural home,

00:06:21.940 --> 00:06:24.670 align:middle line:10%
Hamden, was the last
place I ever imagined.

00:06:24.670 --> 00:06:27.000 align:middle line:10%
I would end up in life.

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:29.460 align:middle line:10%
I'd rather fight
flesh-eating zombies

00:06:29.460 --> 00:06:31.920 align:middle line:10%
in an isolated pocket
of Pennsylvania.

00:06:31.920 --> 00:06:41.050 align:middle line:90%


00:06:41.050 --> 00:06:42.840 align:middle line:90%
My name is Darius James.

00:06:42.840 --> 00:06:44.550 align:middle line:10%
If you're familiar
with me at all,

00:06:44.550 --> 00:06:47.800 align:middle line:10%
it's because I published
two books, "Negrophobia"

00:06:47.800 --> 00:06:51.690 align:middle line:10%
and "That's Blacksploitation,
Roots of the Badass 'Tude"

00:06:51.690 --> 00:06:52.500 align:middle line:10%
back in the '90s.

00:06:52.500 --> 00:07:09.940 align:middle line:90%


00:07:09.940 --> 00:07:13.960 align:middle line:10%
I came back to this
house in January of 2007.

00:07:13.960 --> 00:07:18.220 align:middle line:10%
My time in Berlin had
come to an abrupt end.

00:07:18.220 --> 00:07:21.790 align:middle line:90%
My father had died.

00:07:21.790 --> 00:07:24.880 align:middle line:90%
He was 81 years old.

00:07:24.880 --> 00:07:28.000 align:middle line:84%
All that remained of my
father was his mask collection

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:32.230 align:middle line:84%
and a cardboard box
filled with ashes.

00:07:32.230 --> 00:07:35.320 align:middle line:84%
I have not touched
either since my return.

00:07:35.320 --> 00:07:38.020 align:middle line:84%
My childhood home had
become a mausoleum.

00:07:38.020 --> 00:07:40.800 align:middle line:90%


00:07:40.800 --> 00:07:44.220 align:middle line:84%
I live in this house with
my younger sister, Jerri.

00:07:44.220 --> 00:07:46.770 align:middle line:84%
She is the sweetest
person I know.

00:07:46.770 --> 00:07:49.110 align:middle line:84%
And she is the only
reason why I'm still here.

00:07:49.110 --> 00:08:27.533 align:middle line:90%


00:08:27.533 --> 00:08:30.028 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:30.028 --> 00:09:02.090 align:middle line:90%


00:09:02.090 --> 00:09:05.350 align:middle line:84%
In an early stage of my
search, I went to an exhibition

00:09:05.350 --> 00:09:08.030 align:middle line:84%
at the Caribbean Cultural
Center in Manhattan

00:09:08.030 --> 00:09:11.150 align:middle line:84%
titled "Standing with
Papa Legba, Voodoo

00:09:11.150 --> 00:09:12.800 align:middle line:90%
at the Crossroads."

00:09:12.800 --> 00:09:16.460 align:middle line:84%
It was an unusual look at
Haitian spiritual traditions

00:09:16.460 --> 00:09:18.410 align:middle line:84%
through the lens of
contemporary art.

00:09:18.410 --> 00:09:21.740 align:middle line:90%


00:09:21.740 --> 00:09:25.920 align:middle line:84%
That's where I met its young
curator, Chanterelle Lewis.

00:09:25.920 --> 00:09:29.540 align:middle line:84%
Chanterelle reminds me
of a young Mohammad Ali.

00:09:29.540 --> 00:09:32.450 align:middle line:84%
She has the distinct lines
and grace of a dancer

00:09:32.450 --> 00:09:33.930 align:middle line:90%
and the mind of a boxer.

00:09:33.930 --> 00:09:38.540 align:middle line:90%


00:09:38.540 --> 00:09:41.210 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to know more about her.

00:09:41.210 --> 00:09:44.570 align:middle line:84%
I had a feeling she was more
than professionally involved

00:09:44.570 --> 00:09:47.660 align:middle line:84%
with the themes
of her exhibition.

00:09:47.660 --> 00:09:51.590 align:middle line:84%
So a few weeks later, I dropped
by at her home in Brooklyn.

00:09:51.590 --> 00:10:01.020 align:middle line:90%


00:10:01.020 --> 00:10:02.226 align:middle line:90%
>> Hey.

00:10:02.226 --> 00:10:05.628 align:middle line:90%


00:10:05.628 --> 00:10:08.544 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to mi casa.

00:10:08.544 --> 00:10:10.002 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:10:10.002 --> 00:10:12.440 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:10:12.440 --> 00:10:17.030 align:middle line:10%
>> So I practice Lucumi, which
is a derivative of Yoruba

00:10:17.030 --> 00:10:19.310 align:middle line:10%
spirituality.

00:10:19.310 --> 00:10:25.790 align:middle line:84%
And a basic part of that is
the understanding of the role

00:10:25.790 --> 00:10:30.590 align:middle line:84%
that ancestors play in
your existence and the way

00:10:30.590 --> 00:10:32.530 align:middle line:84%
you move about the
world on a daily basis.

00:10:32.530 --> 00:10:35.090 align:middle line:90%
So your ancestors walk with you.

00:10:35.090 --> 00:10:38.930 align:middle line:84%
They're not just off somewhere
in this random kingdom.

00:10:38.930 --> 00:10:41.260 align:middle line:84%
But they protect you
every single day.

00:10:41.260 --> 00:10:43.670 align:middle line:90%
And so you'll see basic altars.

00:10:43.670 --> 00:10:47.130 align:middle line:90%
You might see glasses of water.

00:10:47.130 --> 00:10:51.020 align:middle line:84%
And again, each glass
representing a different group

00:10:51.020 --> 00:10:52.040 align:middle line:90%
of ancestors.

00:10:52.040 --> 00:10:56.710 align:middle line:84%
>> What days do you actually
acknowledge your ancestors?

00:10:56.710 --> 00:10:58.640 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, this is like
a daily practice.

00:10:58.640 --> 00:11:01.130 align:middle line:84%
I try to acknowledge
them on a daily basis.

00:11:01.130 --> 00:11:04.520 align:middle line:84%
But I generally try to refresh
my altar with the glasses

00:11:04.520 --> 00:11:07.559 align:middle line:90%
of water on Sundays.

00:11:07.559 --> 00:11:10.100 align:middle line:84%
And maybe it has something to
do with my Catholic upbringing,

00:11:10.100 --> 00:11:11.380 align:middle line:90%
the Christian upbringing.

00:11:11.380 --> 00:11:14.990 align:middle line:84%
But that's a day where
I'm starting my week off.

00:11:14.990 --> 00:11:16.720 align:middle line:84%
So I like to do
that on the Sunday.

00:11:16.720 --> 00:11:20.410 align:middle line:84%
>> I understand, yeah it's
kind of interesting too,

00:11:20.410 --> 00:11:25.875 align:middle line:84%
because there's a wall in
my home surrounded by masks

00:11:25.875 --> 00:11:33.550 align:middle line:84%
and things, which is my
family, paternal side.

00:11:33.550 --> 00:11:34.350 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:11:34.350 --> 00:11:35.800 align:middle line:90%
>> My family.

00:11:35.800 --> 00:11:42.080 align:middle line:84%
And although my father insisted
that he wasn't influenced

00:11:42.080 --> 00:11:45.740 align:middle line:84%
by voodoo at all,
everything that I've

00:11:45.740 --> 00:11:47.840 align:middle line:84%
discovered since moving
back in the house

00:11:47.840 --> 00:11:49.300 align:middle line:90%
seems to contradict that.

00:11:49.300 --> 00:11:51.490 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:51.490 --> 00:11:52.370 align:middle line:90%


00:11:52.370 --> 00:11:54.650 align:middle line:84%
On another visit to
New York, I happened

00:11:54.650 --> 00:11:57.200 align:middle line:84%
to be invited to spend the
afternoon in the home of Danny

00:11:57.200 --> 00:11:58.000 align:middle line:90%
Simmons.

00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:00.760 align:middle line:90%


00:12:00.760 --> 00:12:03.280 align:middle line:84%
Danny is a worldly
and unpretentious man

00:12:03.280 --> 00:12:05.980 align:middle line:84%
who is much more than
the sum of his parts,

00:12:05.980 --> 00:12:09.430 align:middle line:84%
painter, writer, art
collector, and, together

00:12:09.430 --> 00:12:12.940 align:middle line:84%
with his Brother Russell,
producer of HBO's "Def

00:12:12.940 --> 00:12:15.610 align:middle line:90%
Poetry Jam."

00:12:15.610 --> 00:12:17.680 align:middle line:84%
He's a system of
refuge and support

00:12:17.680 --> 00:12:20.920 align:middle line:84%
for a broad artistic and
intellectual community

00:12:20.920 --> 00:12:22.185 align:middle line:90%
in New York and beyond.

00:12:22.185 --> 00:12:24.376 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:24.376 --> 00:12:28.690 align:middle line:90%


00:12:28.690 --> 00:12:31.720 align:middle line:10%
Thinking about my father, this
is an extraordinary collection.

00:12:31.720 --> 00:12:36.310 align:middle line:90%


00:12:36.310 --> 00:12:40.840 align:middle line:10%
My father collects
masks from all over.

00:12:40.840 --> 00:12:42.520 align:middle line:10%
And he's got some good pieces.

00:12:42.520 --> 00:12:45.640 align:middle line:90%


00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:48.550 align:middle line:10%
But when I've tried to
talk with him about it

00:12:48.550 --> 00:12:56.660 align:middle line:10%
in the past in terms of
spiritual powers of Africa,

00:12:56.660 --> 00:12:59.890 align:middle line:10%
he was kind of blind to that.

00:12:59.890 --> 00:13:01.780 align:middle line:10%
He was looking at it purely--

00:13:01.780 --> 00:13:03.275 align:middle line:10%
>> From aesthetic reasons?

00:13:03.275 --> 00:13:06.040 align:middle line:10%
>> That's what he
was telling me.

00:13:06.040 --> 00:13:07.780 align:middle line:10%
You know what I'm saying?

00:13:07.780 --> 00:13:10.090 align:middle line:84%
Which kind of led
to this project

00:13:10.090 --> 00:13:15.940 align:middle line:84%
that there are these African
influences in people's lives

00:13:15.940 --> 00:13:19.540 align:middle line:84%
that they don't
want to acknowledge.

00:13:19.540 --> 00:13:27.990 align:middle line:84%
And obviously, based on
what I know about yoy,

00:13:27.990 --> 00:13:32.091 align:middle line:84%
you recognize those powers,
and you respect them.

00:13:32.091 --> 00:13:34.645 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, yeah.

00:13:34.645 --> 00:13:36.270 align:middle line:84%
People have been
taught, and especially

00:13:36.270 --> 00:13:39.900 align:middle line:84%
generations prior
to ours have been

00:13:39.900 --> 00:13:42.150 align:middle line:84%
taught that anything
associated with Africa

00:13:42.150 --> 00:13:45.720 align:middle line:84%
was bad unless it was
an aesthetic thing.

00:13:45.720 --> 00:13:48.060 align:middle line:84%
You can relate to the
aesthetic of a mask,

00:13:48.060 --> 00:13:50.424 align:middle line:84%
or you can relate to
the aesthetic of fabric

00:13:50.424 --> 00:13:51.590 align:middle line:90%
or this, that, or the other.

00:13:51.590 --> 00:13:54.210 align:middle line:84%
But the actual culture,
the actual people, that

00:13:54.210 --> 00:13:55.950 align:middle line:90%
was eschewed.

00:13:55.950 --> 00:13:58.490 align:middle line:84%
You can go to any museum and
you can see African masks.

00:13:58.490 --> 00:14:00.000 align:middle line:90%
But they don't concentrate.

00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:03.500 align:middle line:84%
They call it art, and
it's not really art.

00:14:03.500 --> 00:14:05.970 align:middle line:84%
These are ritual
items and objects

00:14:05.970 --> 00:14:08.450 align:middle line:84%
that people use
for points of power

00:14:08.450 --> 00:14:11.250 align:middle line:84%
and for points of
spiritual reference.

00:14:11.250 --> 00:14:12.780 align:middle line:90%
They don't talk about that.

00:14:12.780 --> 00:14:13.980 align:middle line:90%
And it's eschewed.

00:14:13.980 --> 00:14:18.730 align:middle line:84%
Anything that's non-Christian
in this society that is looked

00:14:18.730 --> 00:14:19.530 align:middle line:90%
at--

00:14:19.530 --> 00:14:22.050 align:middle line:84%
But yet, you can look at the
same object as a European

00:14:22.050 --> 00:14:23.720 align:middle line:84%
and say, oh, this
is a great mask.

00:14:23.720 --> 00:14:27.540 align:middle line:84%
Let me put some wax on it
and shine it up and put it

00:14:27.540 --> 00:14:29.460 align:middle line:90%
next to a Picasso or something.

00:14:29.460 --> 00:14:31.570 align:middle line:84%
But if you start
talking about it

00:14:31.570 --> 00:14:34.950 align:middle line:84%
in its natural setting
as a religious object,

00:14:34.950 --> 00:14:35.790 align:middle line:90%
people get upset.

00:14:35.790 --> 00:14:37.150 align:middle line:90%
And that's what we were taught.

00:14:37.150 --> 00:14:38.130 align:middle line:90%
>> You're 100% right.

00:14:38.130 --> 00:14:41.770 align:middle line:84%
They're afraid, because
they really don't know.

00:14:41.770 --> 00:14:43.590 align:middle line:84%
But if we look a
little deeper, we'll

00:14:43.590 --> 00:14:45.770 align:middle line:90%
see what the truth is in there.

00:14:45.770 --> 00:14:46.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah.

00:14:46.710 --> 00:14:48.880 align:middle line:84%
People have walked in here
and looked at the stuff

00:14:48.880 --> 00:14:50.950 align:middle line:84%
and turned around
and walked out.

00:14:50.950 --> 00:14:54.090 align:middle line:84%
People who talk a lot of black
stuff say, oh, no, no, no, man.

00:14:54.090 --> 00:14:56.896 align:middle line:84%
I can't be in the
room with that stuff.

00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:58.570 align:middle line:90%
>> It's the absence of faith--

00:14:58.570 --> 00:14:59.370 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes

00:14:59.370 --> 00:15:01.050 align:middle line:90%
>> --to begin with, you know?

00:15:01.050 --> 00:15:05.490 align:middle line:84%
And the more we look
at what we have here,

00:15:05.490 --> 00:15:08.310 align:middle line:84%
the more we look and get to
understand and let some of it

00:15:08.310 --> 00:15:11.550 align:middle line:84%
be revealed to you,
then you'll really

00:15:11.550 --> 00:15:12.836 align:middle line:90%
see how fortunate you are.

00:15:12.836 --> 00:15:14.460 align:middle line:84%
>> And you'll see
where you power lies.

00:15:14.460 --> 00:15:15.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:15:15.260 --> 00:15:16.860 align:middle line:84%
>> Your power lies
in your history.

00:15:16.860 --> 00:15:20.174 align:middle line:84%
For me, I started
collecting African art--

